comment_data.body: Previously, when you had IntelliJ open, was it showing a Flutter project when you shut it down? Did you have multiple projects open then? If it was trying to reopen a Flutter project, was the project recently created or something you had been working with for a while?

I closed the project and then opened it via ToolBox. So I clicked on the project in toolbox and then it opens the right project. Beside the error everything works fine except an analysis Issue. It's just a bit nasty to see it but it don't impact me but maybe others so it might be important to fix.

does Flutter work when you run your application from the command line?
Also, can you share the output of running
`flutter --version` on the command line?

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!
Flutter is running, there is no problem beside the "analysis issues". There is the error but I can Flutter run without problems
This looks like an internal IntelliJ error related to Code With Me. Are you using Code With Me?

Yes I'm using code with me. The next time I use IntelliJ, I will deinstall it. It unnecessary for me anyway. But thanks for the tip!
I will keep you posted
I filed https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WEB-52388 to track this problem. Closing this issue.
